==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Manse
<hw>Manse</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>mansa</ets>,
<ets>mansus</ets>, <ets>mansum</ets>, a farm, fr. L. <ets>manere</ets>,
<ets>mansum</ets>, to stay, dwell. See <er>Mansion</er>,
<er>Manor</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A dwelling house, generally with
land attached.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The parsonage; a clergyman's house.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Capital manse</b></col>, <cd>the manor house, or lord's
court.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Manservant</ent>⟦br⟧
